extends default

block content
  h1(style="text-align:center;") Our Favorite Recipes

  //- Recipe 1
  h2 Classic Spaghetti Carbonara
  p
    | This authentic Italian pasta dish is quick, comforting, and absolutely delicious.
    | Creamy sauce, crispy pancetta, and perfectly cooked spaghetti make this a go-to dinner.
  h3 Ingredients:
  ul
    li 400g spaghetti
    li 150g pancetta or guanciale, diced
    li 2 large eggs
    li 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese
    li Salt ans black pepper to taste
  h3 Instructions:
  ol
    li Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup pasta water.
    li In a bowl, whisk eggs and Parmesan together.
    li In a pan, cook pancetta until crispy.
    li Add hot pasta to the pan, remove from heat, and stir in egg-cheese mixture.
    li Add reserved pasta water if needed for creaminess. Season with pepper and serve.

  //- Recipe 2
  h2 Fluffy Blueberry Pancakes
  p
    | Start your morning right with these light and fluffy pancakes bursting with juicy blueberries.
    | Perfect for a lazy Sunday brunch.
  h3 Ingredients:
  ul
    li 1 cup all-purpose flour
    li 1 tbsp sugar
    li 1 tsp baking powder
    li 1/2 tsp baking soda
    li 1/4 tsp salt
    li 1 cup buttermilk
    li 1 large egg
    li 2 tbsp melted butter
    li 1 cup fresh blueberries
  h3 Instructions:
  ol
    li Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
    li In another bowl, whisk buttermilk, egg, and melted butter.
    li Combine wet and dry ingredients until just mixed; fold in blueberries.
    li Heat a skillet, grease lightly, and pour batter to form pancakes.
    li Cook until bubbles form, flip, and cook until golden. Serve with maple syrup.

  //- Recipe 3
  h2 Easy Chicken Stir-Fry
  p
    | A quick and healthy dish loaded with fresh vegetables and tender chicken in a savory sauce.
    | Great for busy weeknights.
  h3 Ingredients:
  ul
    li 2 chicken breasts, sliced thin
    li 2 cups mixed vegetables (broccoli, carrots, bell peppers)
    li 2 tbsp soy sauce
    li 1 tbsp oyster sauce
    li 1 tsp cornstarch mixed with 2 tbsp water
    li 2 tbsp vegetable oil
  h3 Instructions:
  ol
    li Heat oil in a large pan or wok.
    li Stir-fry chicken until golden and cooked through; remove and set aside.
    li Stir-fry vegetables for 3-4 minutes.
    li Add chicken back, pour in sauces, and stir well.
    li Add cornstarch slurry, cook until thickened, and serve over rice.

  //- Recipe 4
  h2 Chocolate Chip Cookies
  p
    | Soft and chewy with gooey chocolate in every bite — a timeless classic.
  h3 Ingredients:
  ul
    li 1 cup butter, softened
    li 1 cup brown sugar
    li 1/2 cup white sugar
    li 2 eggs
    li 2 tsp vanilla extract
    li 3 cups all-purpose flour
    li 1 tsp baking soda
    li 2 cups chocolate chips
  h3 Instructions:
  ol
    li Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
    li Cream butter and sugars until fluffy; beat in eggs and vanilla.
    li Mix in flour and baking soda until just combined; fold in chocolate chips.
    li Scoop onto baking sheet and bake for 8-10 minutes until edges are golden.
    li Cool slightly before serving.